"title": "3257: Holy Spirit, gift of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3257",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the OT the gift of the Holy Spirit was restricted to individuals for particular tasks, but at Pentecost and on subsequent occasions, the Holy Spirit is given to all believers.</p>\n<h2>The gift of the Holy Spirit in the OT</h2>\n<h3>The Spirit is given to individuals for specific tasks</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:6\">1SA 10:6</a> <em>to Saul, for kingship</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:2-Exod31:5\">EXO 31:2–31:5</a> <em>to Bezalel, for craftsmanship</em></p>\n<h3>The gift of the Spirit can be withdrawn</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:14\">1SA 16:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11\">PSA 51:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:20\">JDG 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:24\">1KI 22:24</a></p>\n<h2>The gift of the Holy Spirit is foretold</h2>\n<h3>He is promised by John the Baptist</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11\">MAT 3:11</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:8\">MRK 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:16\">LUK 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:33\">JHN 1:33</a></p>\n<h3>He is promised by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:49\">LUK 24:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:39\">JHN 7:37–7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16\">JHN 14:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7\">JHN 16:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:4-Acts1:5\">ACT 1:4–1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:16\">ACT 11:16</a></p>\n<h2>The gift of the Holy Spirit before Pentecost</h2>\n<h3>Individuals filled with the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:15\">LUK 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:41\">LUK 1:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:67\">LUK 1:67</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:25-Luke2:27\">LUK 2:25–2:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ receives the gift of the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16\">MAT 3:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10\">MRK 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:32\">JHN 1:32</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ bids his disciples receive the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:22\">JHN 20:22</a></p>\n<h2>The gift of the Holy Spirit at Pentecost and after</h2>\n<h3>At Pentecost</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:2-Acts2:4\">ACT 2:2–2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33\">ACT 2:33</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit was given on later occasions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44\">ACT 10:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:15-Acts8:17\">ACT 8:15–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:17\">ACT 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:6\">ACT 19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:5\">GAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a></p>\n<h3>The gift of the Spirit is for all believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38-Acts2:39\">ACT 2:38–2:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17\">ACT 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:32\">ACT 5:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:45\">ACT 10:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:17\">ACT 11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:8\">ACT 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">ROM 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:8\">1TH 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a></p>\n<h3>God's willingness to give the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:13\">LUK 11:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a></p>\n<h2>God's purposes require the gift of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<h3>To give assurance of acceptance by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:8\">ACT 15:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:47\">ACT 10:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:17\">ACT 11:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:24\">1JN 3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:13\">1JN 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>To convict the world of sin</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7-John16:8\">JHN 16:7–16:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:37\">ACT 2:37</a></p>\n<h3>To provide spiritual gifts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:45-Acts10:46\">ACT 10:45–10:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:6\">ACT 19:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:4–12:11</a></p>\n<h3>To work miracles, signs and wonders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:18-Rom15:19\">ROM 15:18–15:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:5\">GAL 3:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a></p>\n<h3>To give boldness in preaching and witnessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">ACT 4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:32\">ACT 5:32</a></p>\n<h3>To cultivate the fruit of the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:5\">ROM 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:13\">ROM 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16\">GAL 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>To sanctify the believer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>",
